      "writtenOn": "2019-03-01T14:57:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "CustomFeatures feels a whole like like SkSL::Program::Inputs, in that (as I understand it) it provides a means for a shader to communicate that it requires a particular piece of information to be provided to it. Do we really need a second channel for this sort of thing?",
