      "writtenOn": "2019-03-01T16:58:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So first of all, this is just how the (pre-sksl) sample locations worked. This is basically just an un-revert.\n\nThat being said, sample locations are a bit more challenging because we have to integrate the render target\u0027s sample locations into the shader key. We do store a render target\u0027s sample locations, but on the first hit, we literally call glGetMultisamplefv(GL_SAMPLE_POSITION, ...) during GrProgramDesc::Build. This flag is how we know we need to query sample locations when setting up the program key.\n\nDo you have any suggestions on how we can make this work with SkSL::Program::Inputs? GrProgramDesc needs to know to add the sample locations to the key for the initial cache lookup, before we even start generating SkSL.",
      "parentUuid": "6e92ed0b_7daef431",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 190,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 202,
        "endChar": 75
      },
      "revId": "7d598d9448d0574e9c42ce33456071d3e2abc8c1",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
